&lt;p&gt;Own the end-to-end strategy and execution of the Tempo Protein category, balancing customer experience, supply continuity, product innovation, and financial performance. This role serves as the primary business owner for the category, partnering cross-functionally to identify opportunities, solve complex problems, and deliver results in a fast-paced, highly visible environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is best suited for someone who enjoys building processes where they don&#39;t yet exist, thrives in a rapidly changing environment, and views ambiguity as an opportunity rather than an obstacle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain category strategy, in service of company-wide goals&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the identification, evaluation, and choice of suppliers and SKUs for the category&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate, negotiate, and manage RFPs with both new and current suppliers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strategic supplier partnerships that foster innovation, improve performance, reduce cost, and strengthen long-term supply continuity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct supply market analysis and collect supplier intelligence to drive sourcing process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with culinary team to identify new ingredient needs and test new suppliers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Cross Functional Partners to ensure all new suppliers meet Home Chef guidelines and expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as point on highly visible new protein A/B and Market tests&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with legal to negotiate contract terms with key supplier partners and ensure terms + conditions of those contracts are managed and met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Procurement Operations, Warehouse and site teams to improve supply chain performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with local sites and supplier partners to problem solve regular supply disruptions and secure product in time for weekly meal production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own category performance, proactively monitoring key metrics including cost, quality, supply continuity, customer feedback, inventory health, and supplier performance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend industry conferences to identify new trends, suppliers and/or ingredients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, prioritize, and commercialize new product opportunities that support customer experience, operational efficiency, and financial goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires 10% travel&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability needed for this role. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, ability and/or other characteristics needed for this role. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of procurement and sourcing experience (food category-related preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in food and beverage industry highly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive-level succinct communication, both verbal and written; discernment when delivering updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong data and numerical orientation; baseline Excel/GSheet knowledge (index/match, pivot tables, gut-checking data)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical mindset with the ability to translate complex data into actionable business recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to independently manage multiple cross-functional initiatives with competing timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lead cross

&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role follows a &lt;strong&gt;Day shift&lt;/strong&gt; schedule, working from &lt;strong&gt;7:00am - 4:00pm&lt;/strong&gt;, with designated days off on&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Saturday &amp;amp; Sunday.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; Schedule may vary based on occasional site needs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Core FSQA Superintendent is responsible for overseeing the implementation, execution, and continuous improvement of core Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality programs at Home Chef. This role ensures compliance with the SQF (Safe Quality Food) Management System, including the development, execution, and monitoring of the cleaning and sanitation program, master sanitation schedule, food safety and quality plan, and pest control management. The Core Superintendent is also accountable for the Management Review process.The FSQA Superintendent leads by example in driving food safety culture.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Support the design, Implementation &amp;amp; Verification of the Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality Management System&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the enforcement and continuous improvement of Home Chef’s Food Safety and Quality Systems, designed to meet regulatory, Food Safety and Quality requirements to assure compliance with SQF requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the development, implementation, and execution of the cleaning and sanitation program, including the Master Sanitation Schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the Management Review process, ensuring that all critical aspects of the FSQA programs are evaluated and improved as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the SQF Practitioner, ensuring compliance with SQF standards and maintaining documentation for audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the gathering, trending and reporting of metrics that effectively measure and communicate performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works closely with the plant FSQA teams and cross-functionally in understanding, identifying gaps and proposing changes to processes that affect quality systems compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a backup to the FSQA Manager during their absence, assuming responsibility for managing quality assurance functions and leading the QA team effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Support Core FSQA Supervisor &amp;amp; Hourly Staff in day to day operations&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond and provide solutions to escalations in a 24/7 production environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide coverage support as needed in a 24/7 production environment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with recruiting teams to adequately staff each shift&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist supervisors in personnel coaching as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Drive Improvements of Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality Management System&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify gaps in programs through internal audit or CAPA&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide thorough corrective actions to deviations and gaps,&amp;nbsp; ensuring that corrective actions are implemented effectively.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to address any non-conformities and drive continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver training to plant FSQA teams related to program rollout&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver communication with plant and corporate stakeholders regarding new or updated programs and any critical issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Develop RTH Supervisory Staff&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead weekly supervisory meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform as subject matter expert

&lt;p&gt;The Engineering Project Manager is an organized, detail-oriented self-starter who leads cross-functional capital projects that support furthering the automation of the production process, maintaining and improving facilities, and enabling additional product lines. This position will collaborate with cross-functional teams, including engineering, operations, supply chain, and vendors, to deliver projects on time and within budget.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple engineering capital projects simultaneously from conception to completion, including defining project scope, schedules, and budgets, identifying resources, managing project risks, and ensuring deliverables meet business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with cross-functional teams to understand business needs and technical requirements, identify project risks and dependencies, and develop project plans that align with business objectives and technical requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide project status updates and manage stakeholder expectations by communicating project progress, milestones, and risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical expertise to identify, evaluate, and implement new technologies and processes that improve production efficiency, quality, and cost-effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all projects comply with relevant codes, standards, and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage project budgets and ensure costs are managed within budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage project documentation, including project plans, technical specifications, and project reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive strong communication between corporate and fulfillment centers to gain buy-in and alignment on initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates a willingness to work flexible hours and travel frequently to fulfillment centers to provide regular on-site support, guidance, and drive accountability, while also developing strong relationships with site teams and local stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires up to 50% travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability needed for this role. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completion of a four-year degree program in a related field: Engineering (Ideally in chemical, industrial, or mechanical)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of managing projects and resources with $100k or greater scope in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of experience in production/operational environments Interpersonal skills to work with team members across functions and in both production and corporate environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical proficiency to meet variable needs of the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to think “outside-the-box”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to react on the fly to unforeseen production and planning scenarios as they arise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer proficiency (i.e., Microsoft Word, Excel, Gmail, PowerPoint)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to track details and to keep track of projectsExcellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Results-oriented attitude; able to multitask and get things done Willingness to embrace change and adjust quickly in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in CAD software, such as AutoCAD, is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;More About Us&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a temporary position, expected to last approximately 6 months.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Container&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Text&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a culinary production expert to lead kitchen operations for Home Chef’s Ready to Heat brand, Tempo. The ideal candidate will have strong attention to detail, an obsession with providing customers the highest-possible quality meals, and the ability to train and lead a team of associates to be able to consistently execute the culinary vision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Oversee product quality in a mass production kitchen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate consistent, premium taste, appearance, and performance of every meal leaving our high-volume kitchen&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and adhere to gold standards of food quality and food safety&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare weekly cook schedules and review/approve payroll in collaboration with HR&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently maintain standards of quality, cost, eye appeal, and flavor of foods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check all processes before production time and inspect the presentation of food items to ensure quality standards are met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with RTH production manager to ensure all ingredients are available when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Train and lead team members through the prep, cooking, and cooling processes&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train, coach, and develop sous chef staff, including weekly 1:1 sessions for their growth and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise, evaluate, and train employees, ensure sanitation and safety, menu planning, and related production activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop training programs and provide professional development opportunities for all kitchen staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Work with Corporate R&amp;amp;D chefs on ingredient and menu continuous improvement opportunities&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the execution of new recipes, training and oversight of kitchen staff to implement new recipes, and collaborate with the R&amp;amp;D team to improve existing recipes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend weekly meetings with R&amp;amp;D chefs in order to give feedback on recipes or ingredient specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review meal ratings weekly and assess areas for performance improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Documentation and Progress Tracking&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure proper documentation and record keeping of lot information, CCP’s, sensory results, and yields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sign off on Assembly Production Sheets, ensuring that meal plating is visually appealing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure batches are properly recorded in Progress Tracker&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires 5% travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Qualifications&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, ability and/or other characteristics needed for this role. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years’ experience in a commissary kitchen and high-volume food preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED or related work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;American Culinary Federation chef certification

&lt;p&gt;As the FSQA Manager, you are the strategic guardian of food safety and quality at our production facility. You will lead a high-performing team to ensure the integrity of two distinct, fast-growing business lines: our signature Meal Kit and our Ready-to-Heat (Tempo) products. This is not just a compliance role; it is a leadership position requiring a strategic mindset to drive continuous improvement, manage complex Tempo risk profiles, bridge the gap between corporate standards and site execution, and serve as a vital member of the Site Management Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Strategic Leadership and Talent Development&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach, train, and develop a multi-shift FSQA team to ensure they possess in-depth knowledge of both raw meal kit and RTH safety principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Production, Warehouse, and Continuous Improvement to integrate food safety into the facility&#39;s daily operational DNA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategically build a talent pipeline at the site level to support business growth and technical complexity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Multi-Platform Governance &amp;amp; Project Management&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the implementation of Home Chef and SQF standards for both business platforms, ensuring consistent compliance with FDA and USDA requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the site SME for FSQA programs, overseeing program pilots, validations, and readiness assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for all regulatory and third-party inspections, managing CAPA activities and systemic root cause investigations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Strategic Improvement &amp;amp; Risk Assessment&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize internal and customer-reported data to identify trends and execute strategic initiatives that reduce errors and enhance the customer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead site-level FSQA risk assessments for new product launches and process changes, ensuring food safety is integrated from concept to consumer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver against key site metrics that reflect broader company business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the Root Cause Analysis (RCA) process for any incidents, ensuring permanent corrective and preventive actions are sustained.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability needed for this role. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in food science, food technology, microbiology, or related field preferred (or 10+ years in FSQA food safety and quality assurance of equivalent high-level success)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7-10 years experience in quality assurance, food safety, food distribution, food manufacturing, supply chain or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record in Ready-to-Eat (RTE) or Ready-to-Heat (RTH) operations is essential; you must understand the nuances of high-risk food environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5 years supervisory experience required with at least 3 years successfully managing multi- shift operations or departments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and oral communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strategic thinker who thrives in fast-paced, evolving environments and can make high-stakes decisions with minimal supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience with GFSI, FDA, and USDA inspections, programs, and expectations

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role follows a &lt;strong&gt;3rd &lt;/strong&gt;shift schedule, working from &lt;strong&gt;9:30 PM to 6:30 AM&lt;/strong&gt;, with designated days off on&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Saturday &amp;amp; Sunday.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Tempo FSQA Supervisor is responsible for driving the food safety and quality control shift functions within Tempo. The role includes a combination of supervision and active participation in the tasks to ensure that all products are safe, consistent, of the highest quality, and meet all requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Planning&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assign daily and weekly responsibilities for RTH FSQA Techs and Sanitors, making sure there are appropriate resources to cover all activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist FSQA RTH Superintendent with development of daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly &amp;amp; annual schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create FSQA Supervisor Recap; document any issues and work with the FSQA RTH Superintendent for resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be aware &amp;amp; proactive on shift metric reporting, understanding report outs &amp;amp; working on plans for improvement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Quality Control:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee RTH FSQA functions for all process steps while working closely with production to help monitor and resolve any issues&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support communications with Production Management regarding any process that does not meet the standard requirements, and work together with necessary parties (e.g., Production Management, Production Team Leads, Production Associates, Maintenance, FSQA Managers and FSQA Associates) to resolve issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct GMP audits and notify production management of violations; work with Production to resolve any issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Food Safety:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform daily, weekly, and/or monthly tasks as assigned by FSQA Superintendent and/or FSQA Leadership including, but not limited to: GMP Audits, Metal Detection Verification, Environmental Monitoring Swabbing, Lab Equipment Calibrations, Chemical Titrations, Pre-Shipment Review, Hold Management, and Start of Line and Pre-Operational Inspections.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold team members and cross-functional partners accountable to Home Chef’s food safety expectations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform Food Safety record verifications including but not limited to: receiving, pre-operational, cook &amp;amp; chill, metal detection and Pre-Shipment Release.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Issue Escalation:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with FSQA Leadership to help resolve food and non-food procurement quality issues within the shift, including but not limited to, questions related to produce quality, portioning quantity, and missing ingredients&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate any decisions to FSQA leadership as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;People Management&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee training programming, holding accountable for delivering all components of the Training program to new RTH FSQA techs and sanitation associates.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train, coach and empower Tempo Quality Techs and Sanitation associates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for performance review and corrective action meetings for Tempo Quality Tech and sanitation associates with FSQA Superintendent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;stro

&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role follows a &lt;strong&gt;2nd&lt;/strong&gt; shift schedule, working from &lt;strong&gt;3:30 PM to 12:30 AM&lt;/strong&gt;, with designated days off on &lt;strong&gt;Saturday and Sunday.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensures the Food Safety and quality of all product labeled, portioned, cooked, MAP, packaged, and shipped from Home Chef Tempo by working alongside production to conduct on-the-line checks of product against recipe specifications and quality standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Verification of CCPs &amp;amp; CQPs&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct inspections at RTH production to ensure Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality requirements are met &amp;amp; recorded in the appropriate form&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verification of the accuracy of ingredients being used for production based on culinary recipe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verification cook &amp;amp; chill temperature limits have been met &amp;amp; documented appropriately&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure post-lethality exposed product is properly stored to prevent cross contamination&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct finished product inspections to ensure product is released according to Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verification of chemical titration prior to each use&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accuracy of labeling for finished products&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct on-line verification checks including but not limited to: Metal Detection, Oxygen Analysis, pH, and seal integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate deviations immediately and assisting with product disposition as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conducting Audits of Production Areas &amp;amp; Pre-requisite programs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct continuous GMP inspections &amp;amp; corrections with proper documentation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspection of equipment &amp;amp; processing area to ensure sanitation &amp;amp; conditions are compliant with Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct frequent environmental monitoring sampling&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce Food Defense protocol as needed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other internal audits as needed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in training of new employees on Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality practices&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Issue Escalation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promptly notifies leadership when Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality issues or HACCP/HACQP deviations arise&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Placing product on FSQA hold and assisting with dispositions as required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting in Production/Sanitation/Safety duties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in non-competitive functions when needed: e.g. sweeping floors, moving product and safety investigations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;General Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow the facility GMP’s and help enforce them throughout the facility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the efforts of the company to maintain our food safety system (SQF) and quality programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attitude and Attendance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Arrives to work at scheduled time and follows time off request procedure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicates with co-workers in a professional manner&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role follows a &lt;strong&gt;Night&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;shift schedule, working from &lt;strong&gt;5:30 PM to 4:30 AM,&lt;/strong&gt; with designated days off on &lt;strong&gt;Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesday.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Gatekeeper is responsible for submitting completed labeled packaging, portions, meal bags and meal kits during their scheduled shift through the production inventory app. The Gatekeeper is expected to submit accurate numbers for inventory and tag WIP (work in progress) live on the production floor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Submit numbers accurately through the production inventory app&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeper will submit accurate numbers of product WIP on the production inventory app&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeper will tag crates for portions, stacks for meal bags and RPCs for meal kits after each submission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeper will ensure that the tag reflects the correct meal, week, quantity, and/or product for every submission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Organize WIP and manage Decant Zone&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeper will push portion stacks to the correct WIP lane after submission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeper will push meal bag stacks to the correct FIFO lane after submission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeper will ensure that sensitive items portioned are pushed to the correct storage location after submission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeper is responsible for turnover of overproduced WIP that can be reallocated to future menus with the shelf life approval of FSQA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeper owns the over decanted pre-portioned zone.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;They will monitor and assign to current week meals for leads to pull from prior to opening cases.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If not being used on current week, they will research and assign to upcoming menus - clearly labeling for easy retrieval&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If not being used on any menus listed in Ops Apps they will count and discard; logging as waste on the waste tracker&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Maintain FIFO&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that the newest product is staged in the back of each WIP lane to ensure that the new WIP is used last.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Audit WIP and report any discrepancies&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeper will conduct audits of submission against WIP to catch any potential submission errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires 0% travel.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Qualifications&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, ability and/or other characteristics needed for this role. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General high school degree, or equivalent, (e.g. GED)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer skills (PC or laptop use, Microsoft Office, Basic Typing)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong math and counting skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
