&lt;p&gt;The Maintenance Superintendent is responsible for hands-on, day to day preventative and corrective maintenance for all Home Chef equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Operational Efficiency:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;and coordinate the daily operations of the maintenance department.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor equipment and systems to ensure efficiency and functionality. Lead projects in coordination with all plant departments to maximize utilization of automation / equipment to improve overall efficiencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with other departments and external contractors or vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages the CMMS and ensures work orders are closed in a timely manner. Plan, schedule, and manage maintenance activities to ensure minimal disruption to operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritizes emergency as well as planned work orders to keep operations running and the equipment running reliably&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage budgets, forecast costs, and ensure the department operates within financial constraints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare maintenance reports and other documentation as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops Preventative Maintenance tasks to keep equipment reliable for all existing and future equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages spare parts inventory for all equipment and maintenance needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts trends of work orders to understand which assets are bad actors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acts as site point of contact for all capital improvement work and helps manage project progress when corporate project manager is not on site&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Training, Planning &amp;amp; Execution:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with health, safety, and environmental regulations from team members and contractors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trains all maintenance team members on how to complete PMs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists CI Manager with overall training and development of members of the CI team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plans day to day maintenance activities for the maintenance team and contractors&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures all planned work is executed for the maintenance team and contractors&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures all emergency work is prioritized and completed to prevent impact to operations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Food &amp;amp; Employee Safety:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures all equipment that is worked on is released to sanitation before returning to the operations team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures all maintenance team members are trained and retrained on safe work practices (LOTO, elevated work, hot work, confined space, line breaks)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforces safety standards and safe work practices for all Home Chef employees and contractors working on site.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;SOPs &amp;amp; Audits&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures maintenance SOPs are developed and maintained up to date&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures documentation on all maintenance tasks are compliant with Food Safety best practices to ensure we are audit ready&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Leadership&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicates with other plant leaders on required maintenance work that could impact operations or put team members at risk&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commun

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role follows a &lt;strong&gt;1st shift &lt;/strong&gt;schedule, working hours are&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;7:00 AM - 3:30 PM&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;with designated days off on&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Friday &amp;amp; Saturday.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Maintenance Technician is responsible for conducting all repairs and preventative maintenance on facility and production equipment. They are responsible for ensuring that the production team has no barriers with production equipment and that contractors are coordinated when completing scheduled service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Employee and Food Safety&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts all work in accordance with sound safety practices and proper work methods or procedures; wears all personal protective equipment (PPE) as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complies with all environmental laws and regulations for chemicals and lubricants as well as disposal and storage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs work in accordance with all quality systems requirements and understands what Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP’s) are and is willing and able to fully support these requirements&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts routine safety checks on the production equipment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Equipment Maintenance&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Services and maintains production-related equipment, which includes motors, conveyors, vibratory fillers, tub washer, flow wrapper, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Installs new production equipment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides guidance and training to machine operators to increase efficiency and reduce downtime on production equipment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reads and interprets equipment manuals to troubleshoot equipment and to assess functionality&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quickly learns how to properly maintain and repair any new equipment brought onsite&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executes Preventative Maintenance Plans On All Equipment As Scheduled by The Maintenance Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains records of PMs and emergency work in the CMMS for equipment history&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies what spare parts are needed and communicates with the Maintenance Manager when they need to be ordered to maintain equipment uptime&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Facility Maintenance&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for keeping the facility in good working order and in compliance with all safety requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinates work orders related to facility improvements and repairs such as dock door and dock leveler repairs, plumbing repairs, building access control, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversees contractors conducting facility repairs on the air compressor, hot water heater, and the fire suppression system&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documents work related to facility improvements and repairs in the Home Chef CMMS to maintain history&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains records of equipment related to compliance requirements such as pH probes, condenser water treatment, or ammonia sensors&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Maintenance Shop Organization&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Directly responsible for making the maintenance shop audit ready at all times, this includes but is not limited to properly storing flammable lubricants and maintaining records of critical safety equipment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keeps the shop tools and spare parts we

&lt;p&gt;The Menu Strategy Analyst will assist with planning the Home Chef Ecommerce menus. This requires involvement in the meal R&amp;amp;D process/planning, supporting the menu development, execution process, and maintenance of menu planning tools and KPI tracking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Menu Planning&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the balancing and publishing process with tactical inputs in Home Chef systems (e.g. Admin) for Core, Family, and Extras menus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform ad-hoc analysis requests to identify and implement actionable takeaways for future menus&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect cross-functional menu requests and ensure execution including but not limited to aging inventory depletions, partnership requests, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively with both menu team and cross functional partners on strategic recommendations for solving menu issues (e.g. over/under food cost, cross functional meeting representative)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Menu Performance Tracking&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute weekly and monthly KPI tracking and analysis of menus - including financial (revenue, food, and margin) metrics and other quantitative (rating) or qualitative (reviews) metrics; this can also include helping track acquisition or marketing promotions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track competitor product offerings and promotions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support development and maintenance of R&amp;amp;D and various Menu Strategy team tools within Google Workspace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;R&amp;amp;D Process Planning &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the meal selection process including preparing the data, leading the meeting, and allocating meals to menus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support weekly recipe ideation process identifying redundancies in concepts and aggregating feedback for discussion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taste and provide feedback on new meals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead sampling for Extras program - preparing items, tracking results, and communicating next steps with cross-functional partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;General Menu Maintenance&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review weekly menus to ensure all products (e.g. meal kits, extras) are merchandised / assigned accurately and meet production guardrails&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute any ad-hoc menu changes and communicate changes to cross-functional partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review bank of successful recipes for future menu uses including reviewing ongoing weekly meal performance for bank consideration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability needed for this role. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completion of a four-year degree program in a related field&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in a rigorous fast-paced work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage multiple complex projects and initiatives simultaneously with a results-oriented approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel/Google sheets experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independent self-starter inclined towards finding solutions without significant oversight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for food and must be able to taste and provide thorough feedback on every meal and ingredient sample test in the kitchen (includes vegetarian, pork, chicken, steak, and seafood)

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Plant Associate Recruiter is responsible for leading the recruitment of on-site&amp;nbsp; production, quality and warehouse positions. The Plant Associate Recruiter is responsible for assisting with the full cycle recruiting, including the onboarding of new hires. The Plant Associate Recruiter responsibilities include conducting initial screenings, scheduling interviews, and making hiring decisions for hourly roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Recruiting&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists our search for top talent for open positions at the facility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruits active and passive candidates from various resources, including campus activities, Internet job boards, social media and employee referrals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops relationships with prospective hires, providing a positive first impression of Home Chef.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists location in the hiring process for open positions, including interviewing and screening applicants both over the phone and in person.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures accurate, professional&amp;nbsp; and timely candidate communications .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follows up on interviewees, interview panels, and sends offers to selected candidates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitors and applies HR recruiting best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains Applicant Tracking System (ATS) in up-to-date and in an organized fashion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other recruiters, helping recruit for other locations as required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Onboarding&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
